steps.instruction:
### Prep
- Mince garlic
- Mince ginger
- Cut lemon into wedges


### Glaze

1. Preheat oven to 425F
2. Heat 1 tablespoon of oil in a small saucepan over low heat
3. Once heated, add garlic and ginger.
4. Cook for about 3 minutes
5. Add in honey and soy sauce
6. Cook for 10 minutes, stirring occasionaly 
7. Turn off heat
8. Whisk in butter
9. Season with salt and pepper to taste


### Chicken
10. Put thighs onto a foil lined baking sheet
11. Season all over with kosher salt and pepper to taste
12. Add half of the glaze along with the remaining 1 tablespoon of oil
13. Toss chicken to coat
14. Put in an even layer on sheet, skin side up
15. Bake for 15 minutes
16. Brush with 2 tablespoons of glaze
17. Roast until golden, about 10 more minutes
18. Serve with a drizzle of glaze on top with rice and a lemon wedge
